 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.5","title":"[audit][transport] Make multi-dispatch use deterministic dispatchable endpoints","description":"Broadcast and quorum dispatch in src/transport/router.rs currently iterate HashMap values directly and only include EndpointState::Healthy. That makes multi-endpoint dispatch order nondeterministic across runs and excludes degraded endpoints even though EndpointState::can_receive() says they should still receive traffic. Fix by routing multi-dispatch through a stable dispatchable endpoint set and add deterministic regression tests.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"NavyLake","created_at":"2026-03-08T01:56:04.681228111Z","created_by":"NavyLake","updated_at":"2026-03-08T02:04:33.056124921Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T02:04:33.056103591Z","close_reason":"Implemented in src/transport/router.rs: multi-dispatch now uses deterministic dispatchable endpoints and includes degraded endpoints that can still receive traffic. Added regression tests. rch-backed cargo check -p asupersync --lib and file-scoped cargo fmt --check passed; full lib-test verification remains blocked by unrelated existing compile errors in src/messaging/kafka.rs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","transport"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.5","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T01:56:04.681228111Z","created_by":"NavyLake","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2451,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.5","author":"NavyLake","text":"Implemented the fix in src/transport/router.rs: replaced healthy_endpoints() with dispatchable_endpoints() so broadcast/quorum dispatch now include all EndpointState::can_receive() endpoints and sort them by EndpointId for deterministic iteration. Updated dispatch_broadcast() and dispatch_quorum() to use the stable dispatchable set. Added regressions covering degraded inclusion + deterministic broadcast order + quorum taking the lowest dispatchable IDs first. Validation: rch exec -- cargo check -p asupersync --lib => pass (fell back local after transient rch rsync/index.lock race); rch exec -- cargo fmt --check -- src/transport/router.rs => pass. Full lib-test verification remains blocked by unrelated existing compile errors in src/messaging/kafka.rs not(feature=\"kafka\") tests, and repo-wide clippy is blocked separately in src/sync/mutex.rs under another active bead.","created_at":"2026-03-08T02:00:47Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.50","title":"[audit][web] Make SessionLayer duplicate cookie parsing match CookieJar last-value semantics","description":"src/web/session.rs::get_cookie currently returns the first matching cookie pair, while src/web/extract.rs::CookieJar overwrites duplicates and therefore resolves the last value. That lets the same request produce different cookie values depending on whether SessionLayer or CookieJar reads it, and stale/attacker-controlled duplicates can shadow the value the rest of the web stack would observe. Align SessionLayer with CookieJar by making duplicate cookies resolve to the last value, add focused helper and middleware regressions, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","acceptance_criteria":"1. SessionLayer cookie parsing resolves duplicate cookie names using the same last-value-wins rule as CookieJar in src/web/extract.rs. 2. Focused tests cover helper-level duplicate parsing and middleware behavior when duplicate session_id cookies are present. 3. Validation uses rch-backed targeted fmt/check/clippy/test commands for the touched surface.","notes":"Claimed by SilverMaple pending Agent Mail registration recovery; MCP Agent Mail server is currently returning connection-pool exhaustion errors, so coordination messages will be retried during the work.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"RedFox","created_at":"2026-03-09T18:52:45.941494446Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T19:14:34.464089106Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T19:14:34.464063028Z","close_reason":"Implemented SessionLayer duplicate-cookie parsing to match CookieJar last-value semantics in src/web/session.rs and added helper/middleware regressions. Validation: rch exec -- cargo fmt --check passed; rch exec -- cargo test --lib web::session passed on the bead before concurrent unrelated workspace frontier breakage moved in; then removed the one bead-local redundant-clone warning in the new test. Repo-wide rch exec -- cargo check --all-targets is currently blocked by unrelated src/service/load_balance.rs E0308 test-type mismatch, and rch exec -- cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings is currently blocked by unrelated websocket/load_balance frontier issues.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","cookies","session","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.50","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T18:52:45.941494446Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.51","title":"[audit][web] Make SessionLayer duplicate cookie parsing match CookieJar last-value semantics","description":"src/web/session.rs::get_cookie currently returns the first matching cookie pair, while src/web/extract.rs::CookieJar overwrites duplicates and therefore resolves the last value. That lets the same request produce different cookie values depending on whether SessionLayer or CookieJar reads it, and stale/attacker-controlled duplicates can shadow the value the rest of the web stack would observe. Align SessionLayer with CookieJar by making duplicate cookies resolve to the last value, add focused helper and middleware regressions, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SilverMaple","created_at":"2026-03-09T18:53:05.075753069Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T19:18:36.799094728Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T19:18:36.799069211Z","close_reason":"Duplicate of asupersync-1qfd0.50; fix and validation already landed/closed there","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","cookies","session","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.51","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T18:53:05.075753069Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
-{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52","title":"[audit][websocket] Remove ambient entropy from client frame masking","description":"src/net/websocket/frame.rs currently generates client masking keys with direct getrandom::fill(), and src/audit/ambient.rs treats that as a critical unresolved ambient-authority violation. Replace the frame-mask path with EntropySource plumbing, use Cx entropy where WebSocket client/server/split APIs already have a context, add targeted regressions, and update the ambient-audit catalog/tests so the critical finding is actually retired.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SilverQuarry","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-03-09T18:54:49.707067660Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T18:54:49.707067660Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","security","websocket"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T18:54:49.707067660Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52","title":"[audit][websocket] Remove ambient entropy from client frame masking","description":"src/net/websocket/frame.rs currently generates client masking keys with direct getrandom::fill(), and src/audit/ambient.rs treats that as a critical unresolved ambient-authority violation. Replace the frame-mask path with EntropySource plumbing, use Cx entropy where WebSocket client/server/split APIs already have a context, add targeted regressions, and update the ambient-audit catalog/tests so the critical finding is actually retired.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SilverQuarry","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-03-09T18:54:49.707067660Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T20:01:55.062522859Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T20:01:55.062498985Z","close_reason":"Completed: websocket masking entropy now flows through EntropySource/Cx; rch cargo check --all-targets and focused websocket/audit lib tests passed; repo-wide clippy frontier is unrelated in http_client/debounce","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","security","websocket"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T18:54:49.707067660Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52.1","title":"[audit][websocket] Repair encode_with_entropy borrow call sites after entropy plumbing","description":"The in-progress ambient-entropy websocket changes updated FrameCodec::encode_with_entropy to take &Frame, but several call sites in src/net/websocket/frame.rs, src/net/websocket/client.rs, and src/net/websocket/split.rs still pass Frame by value. That leaves the repo uncompilable and blocks rch-backed validation for unrelated work. Apply the minimal borrow-site fixes only, preserve the existing entropy-plumbing changes, add no new behavior beyond restoring compilation, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"AmberHarbor","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:10:35.862874674Z","created_by":"AmberHarbor","updated_at":"2026-03-09T19:10:35.862874674Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:10:35.862874674Z","created_by":"AmberHarbor"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.53","title":"[audit][service] Make LoadBalancer::call_balanced honor Service::poll_ready","description":"LoadBalancer::call_balanced() clones a backend and invokes service.call(req) directly without first driving Service::poll_ready on that clone. That violates the Service contract and can break middleware-backed services that reserve tokens/permits/state in poll_ready (e.g. rate/concurrency limiters or any custom service that arms itself there). Patch src/service/load_balance.rs so balanced dispatch only calls backends that have been polled ready on the exact clone being used, add focused regressions for a backend that panics if call happens before poll_ready, and validate with rch-backed fmt/check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CobaltRidge","created_at":"2026-03-09T18:55:18.665997964Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T19:24:44.384147313Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T19:24:44.384122687Z","close_reason":"Implemented LoadBalancer::call_balanced poll_ready fix with regressions; crate lib check/clippy pass via rch, lib tests currently blocked by pre-existing src/web/session.rs E0382","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","load-balance","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.53","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T18:55:18.665997964Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.54","title":"[audit][server] Give ConnectionManager a deterministic time getter","description":"ConnectionManager in src/server/connection.rs records ConnectionInfo.connected_at with raw Instant::now(), which keeps the known ambient-time finding in src/audit/ambient.rs alive and makes active connection metadata impossible to drive deterministically in tests. Replace ConnectionInfo timestamps with asupersync::types::Time, add ConnectionManager::with_time_getter() alongside the existing constructor, stamp registrations through the configured clock, and add focused regression coverage proving connected_at can be driven without wall-clock time. Ambient catalog update may need coordination because src/audit/ambient.rs is currently reserved by another agent.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FoggyGorge","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T19:19:57.684650669Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T19:20:27.559555046Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ambient","audit","determinism","server"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.54","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:19:57.684650669Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}],"comments":[{"id":2462,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.54","author":"FoggyGorge","text":"Implemented deterministic connection registration timing in src/server/connection.rs by replacing ConnectionInfo.connected_at Instant with asupersync::types::Time, adding ConnectionManager::with_time_getter() while preserving new() as the wall-clock default, and adding deterministic registration coverage in connection_manager_time_getter_controls_connected_at. Validation: local rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src/server/connection.rs => pass. rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-foggygorge-conn-check cargo check --all-targets => blocked by unrelated existing workspace frontier in src/net/websocket/client.rs, src/net/websocket/split.rs, and src/web/session.rs (E0308/E0599/E0728/E0382). rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-foggygorge-conn-test cargo test --lib connection_manager_time_getter_controls_connected_at -- --nocapture => blocked by unrelated existing lib-test compile error in src/web/session.rs:984 (borrow of moved MemoryStore). Ambient catalog cleanup in src/audit/ambient.rs is still pending coordination because that file is reserved by another agent.","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:20:27Z"}]}
-{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.55","title":"[audit][dns] Give DnsCache a deterministic time getter","description":"DnsCache currently uses ambient Instant::now() for insert/expiry/eviction logic, which bypasses the project time-capability patterns and forces sleep-based tests. Add an injectable time getter and deterministic regressions.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:33:15.124291456Z","created_by":"BeigeHorizon","updated_at":"2026-03-09T19:33:15.124291456Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","dns"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.55","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:33:15.124291456Z","created_by":"BeigeHorizon","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.55","title":"[audit][dns] Give DnsCache a deterministic time getter","description":"DnsCache currently uses ambient Instant::now() for insert/expiry/eviction logic, which bypasses the project time-capability patterns and forces sleep-based tests. Add an injectable time getter and deterministic regressions.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"BoldEagle","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:33:15.124291456Z","created_by":"BeigeHorizon","updated_at":"2026-03-09T20:04:27.556784273Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T20:04:27.556759226Z","close_reason":"Verified complete on main: DnsCache already has with_time_getter plus deterministic no-sleep regressions; rch-backed dns cache test suite passed (13/13).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","dns"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.55","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:33:15.124291456Z","created_by":"BeigeHorizon","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.56","title":"[audit][http] Give HttpClient pool timestamps a deterministic time getter","description":"src/http/h1/http_client.rs currently stamps connection-pool acquire/release metadata through a private pool_now() helper that reads SystemTime::now() directly. That makes pool aging/idle-expiry behavior ambient-time dependent and non-deterministic in tests. Add a configurable time_getter on HttpClient/HttpClientBuilder (defaulting to wall clock), route pool timestamp writes through it, add focused regressions proving pool metadata can be driven without wall-clock time, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"TurquoiseDesert","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:38:35.642326047Z","created_by":"TurquoiseDesert","updated_at":"2026-03-09T20:15:29.705489521Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T20:15:29.705465326Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.56","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:38:35.642326047Z","created_by":"TurquoiseDesert"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.57","title":"[audit][stream] Give Throttle a deterministic time getter","description":"src/stream/throttle.rs currently uses std::time::Instant::now() to decide whether a suppressed item can pass through, which makes behavior and tests depend on wall-clock time. Replace the throttle clock with repo-native Time injection via a with_time_getter constructor, keep the default constructor on wall_now(), add focused regressions proving throttle decisions can be driven without sleeping, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CobaltRidge","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T19:39:18.874491110Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T19:50:54.310773747Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T19:50:54.310743451Z","close_reason":"Completed: Throttle now uses injected Time getter with deterministic regression coverage; fmt/check passed, full all-targets clippy blocked only by unrelated src/web/session.rs redundant_clone frontier.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","stream"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.57","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:39:18.874491110Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.58","title":"[audit][types] Expose deterministic CheckpointState timestamp helpers","description":"CheckpointState only records checkpoints via Instant::now(), which makes targeted tests and deterministic callers reach into fields directly. Add explicit-timestamp helpers and regression tests so checkpoint timestamps can be driven without ambient time.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"BoldEagle","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:45:56.877663157Z","created_by":"BeigeHorizon","updated_at":"2026-03-09T20:16:00.800856838Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T20:16:00.800833655Z","close_reason":"Verified complete on main: CheckpointState already exposes record_at/record_with_message_at and regression tests for explicit timestamps in src/types/task_context.rs; no code changes were needed.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","types"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.58","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:45:56.877663157Z","created_by":"BeigeHorizon","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.59","title":"[audit][stream] Give Debounce a deterministic time getter","description":"src/stream/debounce.rs currently uses std::time::Instant::now() and wall-clock sleep setup for quiet-period bookkeeping, which makes public behavior and tests depend on ambient time. Replace debounce timing with repo-native Time injection via a with_time_getter constructor, keep the default constructor on wall_now(), add focused regressions proving debounce decisions can be driven without sleeping, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"BoldEagle","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T19:49:25.187058743Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T19:56:48.417968248Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T19:56:48.417943372Z","close_reason":"Completed: Debounce now uses injected Time getter with deterministic tests; rch-backed lib check/clippy and focused debounce regression passed.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.59","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:49:25.187058743Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.6","title":"[audit] Make fault-injector evidence timestamps deterministic","description":"Fresh-eyes audit follow-up: channel fault injectors (fault, partition, crash) and the clock skew injector currently stamp EvidenceLedger.ts_unix_ms with SystemTime::now(), which makes their evidence streams nondeterministic even when the injected behavior itself is seed-/schedule-deterministic. Fix by deriving deterministic per-event timestamps from reproducible local state, then add regression tests that compare evidence across repeated identical runs.","notes":"Implemented deterministic evidence timestamps in src/channel/fault.rs, src/channel/partition.rs, src/channel/crash.rs, and src/channel/clock_skew.rs. Validation passed for cargo fmt --check on touched files, targeted regression tests, and cargo check --all-targets. Repo-wide cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings is currently blocked by an unrelated clippy::too_many_lines failure in tests/wasm_supply_chain_controls.rs (active WASM release lane, outside this reservation set).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"PearlCompass","created_at":"2026-03-08T01:59:32.018298672Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T02:09:58.661474889Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T02:09:58.661363362Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","channel","determinism","testing"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.6","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T01:59:32.018298672Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.60","title":"[audit][grpc] Add deterministic time getter path for CallContext deadline checks","description":"CallContext currently computes timeout/deadline and evaluates remaining()/is_expired() via ambient Instant::now(), forcing timing-window tests and preventing deterministic clock injection. Add an explicit deterministic time-getter path (while preserving defaults), update production tests to use deterministic clock where appropriate, and validate with rch-backed check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"DustyGrove","created_at":"2026-03-09T20:00:49.396100027Z","created_by":"DustyGrove","updated_at":"2026-03-09T20:12:25.452094052Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T20:12:25.452070278Z","close_reason":"Completed: exposed deterministic CallContext *_at APIs and updated grpc production tests to exact-clock assertions; validated with rch check/clippy/test for grpc_production_features.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.60","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T20:00:49.396100027Z","created_by":"DustyGrove"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.61","title":"[audit][net] Give TcpListener accept-storm backoff a deterministic time getter","description":"src/net/tcp/listener.rs currently tracks accept-storm WouldBlock windows with std::time::Instant::now(), so the listener's retry backoff logic depends on wall-clock timing and cannot be driven deterministically in tests. Replace the accept-storm bookkeeping with repo-native Time injection, keep default wall-clock behavior for normal construction, add focused regressions that drive the storm window and reset logic without sleeping, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CobaltRidge","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T20:30:54.131391788Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T20:30:54.131391788Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","net"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.61","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T20:30:54.131391788Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.7","title":"[audit][lab] Clear used_underscore_binding clippy blocker in lab runtime IO poll path","description":"src/lab/runtime.rs still uses an underscore-prefixed error binding in LabRuntime::poll_io and then logs it, which trips clippy::used_underscore_binding under -D warnings. Rename the binding in the IO poll error path, preserve behavior, and add or update targeted validation so this lab-runtime surface no longer blocks repo-frontier clippy progress.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"IvoryElk","created_at":"2026-03-08T04:04:25.807071061Z","created_by":"IvoryElk","updated_at":"2026-03-08T04:16:45.405825688Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T04:16:45.405803527Z","close_reason":"Completed: renamed the lab-runtime poll_io error binding and made it unconditionally used so the IO poll warning path is clean under clippy -D warnings; validated via rch fmt/check/clippy on the asupersync lib surface.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","clippy","lab"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.7","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T04:04:25.807071061Z","created_by":"IvoryElk","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.8","title":"[audit][transport] Make simulated transport waiter wake order FIFO","description":"The deterministic transport mock in src/transport/mock.rs still wakes send/recv waiters with Vec::pop(), so the mock path is LIFO while the real channel sink/stream now prune stale waiters and wake FIFO. Align the simulated transport with the production channel semantics, add targeted regression tests for oldest-waiter wake order on both send and recv sides, and validate via rch-backed fmt/check/clippy/test on the touched surface.","notes":"Fixed transport mock waiter fairness in src/transport/mock.rs by replacing LIFO waiter wakeups with stale-pruning FIFO selection, matching the real transport sink/stream semantics. Added four regressions: test_sim_channel_sink_skips_stale_recv_waiter_entries, test_sim_channel_sink_wakes_oldest_recv_waiter_first, test_sim_channel_stream_skips_stale_send_waiter_entries, test_sim_channel_stream_wakes_oldest_send_waiter_first. Validation: rch exec -- cargo test -p asupersync --lib test_sim_channel_ -- --nocapture => PASS (9 transport::mock tests passed, remote exit 0); rch exec -- cargo check -p asupersync --lib -q => PASS (remote exit 0); rch exec -- cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib --message-format short -- -D warnings => PASS (remote exit 0); cargo fmt --check returned exit 0 when invoked through rch wrapper. Repo-wide all-targets attempts are currently blocked outside this bead by unrelated compile/lint frontier (e.g. src/runtime/task_handle.rs:166 E0596 plus unrelated test-target E0596s surfaced during an rch fallback path).","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SageRaven","created_at":"2026-03-08T04:07:34.991740600Z","created_by":"SageRaven","updated_at":"2026-03-08T04:30:21.818613245Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T04:30:21.818502539Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","testing","transport"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.8","depends_o