 {"id":"asupersync-3qv04.5.7","title":"[WASM][Framework] Provide explicit unsupported-runtime guards and actionable diagnostics","description":"Make misuse failures intentional and helpful. Browser Edition is not meant to run as a direct runtime in every JS environment, so the package surfaces and framework adapters need explicit unsupported-runtime guards with actionable diagnostics instead of opaque import-time or bootstrap-time crashes.\n\nThis bead covers user-visible errors and guidance for accidental server-side imports, Node/edge misuse, missing browser capabilities, or incompatible package entrypoints. It exists to make the system kinder and faster to debug for real consumers.","notes":"Implemented explicit unsupported-runtime diagnostics across the browser/react/next package surfaces.\n\nDelivered:\n- packages/browser/src/index.ts: Browser runtime capability snapshot, support diagnostics, actionable unsupported-runtime error construction/assertion, and guards in createBrowserRuntime/createBrowserScope\n- packages/react/src/index.ts: React-specific runtime support diagnostics/assertion path with package-specific error identity\n- packages/next/src/index.ts: Next client/server/edge runtime target diagnostics with explicit non-client guidance\n- tests/wasm_js_exports_coverage_contract.rs: contract markers for browser/react/next unsupported-runtime helpers\n\nValidation (all via rch):\n- cargo test --test wasm_js_exports_coverage_contract -- --nocapture ✅ (24 passed)\n- cargo check --test wasm_js_exports_coverage_contract ✅\n- cargo clippy --test wasm_js_exports_coverage_contract -- -D warnings ✅\n- cargo fmt --check -- tests/wasm_js_exports_coverage_contract.rs ✅","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"CyanGrove","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-06T15:14:01.493441539Z","created_by":"CopperForest","updated_at":"2026-03-07T09:36:48.511513431Z","closed_at":"2026-03-07T09:36:48.511463828Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["diagnostics","framework","ux","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-3qv04.5.7","depends_on_id":"asupersync-3qv04.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-06T15:20:19.040950815Z","created_by":"CopperForest","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-3qv04.5.7","depends_on_id":"asupersync-3qv04.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-06T15:14:01.493441539Z","created_by":"CopperForest","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-3qv04.5.7","depends_on_id":"asupersync-3qv04.5.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-06T15:20:04.899138632Z","created_by":"CopperForest","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
